---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/")
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;

const galleryPhotos = [
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-studio-bed.webp`,
    alt: "The bed and compact studio space inside The Retreat",
    caption: "Studio bed beneath exposed beams",
    width: 975,
    height: 1300,
  },
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-practice-room.webp`,
    alt: "A quiet sitting and practice area inside The Retreat",
    caption: "Practice and sitting space",
    width: 975,
    height: 1300,
  },
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-kitchen.webp`,
    alt: "The compact self-catering kitchen with a cooker inside The Retreat",
    caption: "Compact self-catering kitchen",
    width: 975,
    height: 1300,
  },
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-shower-room.webp`,
    alt: "The separate shower room inside The Retreat",
    caption: "Separate shower room",
    width: 975,
    height: 1300,
  },
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-garden.webp`,
    alt: "Trees and green garden space around The Retreat",
    caption: "Garden and trees around the cabin",
    width: 1300,
    height: 975,
  },
  {
    src: `${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-patio-view.webp`,
    alt: "A view from The Retreat doorway across the patio and garden",
    caption: "View from the cabin door",
    width: 975,
    height: 1300,
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Retreat | Still Ground"
  description="A tiny solo retreat cabin in Oulton, near Aylsham, Norfolk, available for 5 to 28 night self-catering retreat stays."
>
  <section class="hero retreat-hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Oulton, nr Aylsham, Norfolk · Solo stays 5 to 28 nights</p>
      <h1>The Retreat</h1>
      <p class="retreat-tagline">A space that holds you.</p>
      <p class="lede">
        A tiny private cabin in rural Norfolk, available to solo retreat guests
        for stays of 5 to 28 nights. No WiFi. No television. Limited phone
        signal. A half-acre garden surrounded by farmland, birds, and quiet.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@stillground.co.uk">Enquire</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="#details">Practical details</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figure class="hero-media">
      <img
        src={`${base}assets/retreat-cottage/retreat-cottage-exterior.webp`}
        alt="The brick exterior of The Retreat beside the garden"
        width="1800"
        height="1350"
        decoding="async"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
      <figcaption>The Retreat</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="statement">
    <p>
      For the right person, the size is the point. Everything is within reach.
      There is nowhere to be except here.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section photo-gallery" aria-labelledby="retreat-gallery-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Gallery</p>
    <h2 id="retreat-gallery-heading">Inside and outside The Retreat</h2>
    <p>
      A first look at the cabin, garden, and practical spaces for a solo
      self-catering retreat.
    </p>
    <div class="gallery-grid">
      {
        galleryPhotos.map((photo) => (
          <figure>
            <img
              src={photo.src}
              alt={photo.alt}
              width={photo.width}
              height={photo.height}
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
            <figcaption>{photo.caption}</figcaption>
          </figure>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split" id="details">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Before you book</p>
      <h2>This is a very small space, intentionally</h2>
      <p>
        The Retreat is a brick-built single-storey cabin, something like a
        brick-built shepherd's hut. Its dimensions are 22 feet long by 7 feet
        wide.
      </p>
      <p>
        Past guests have been surprised by the size, so it is important to be
        honest about this. There is one room: a studio bedsit with exposed beams
        and a small wall window. A separate shower room. A compact but
        well-equipped kitchen. That's it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-panel">
      <p class="small-label">At a glance</p>
      <ul class="list-clean">
        <li>Solo guests only.</li>
        <li>Minimum stay 5 nights, maximum stay 28 nights.</li>
        <li>No WiFi, no TV, limited phone signal.</li>
        <li>Self-catering, with a properly equipped kitchen.</li>
        <li>Separate shower room.</li>
        <li>Off-road parking for one car.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-grid" aria-label="Inside The Retreat">
    <article>
      <h3>Studio bedsit</h3>
      <p>
        A single studio space with exposed beamed ceiling, small wall window,
        and double sofa bed.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Practice space</h3>
      <p>
        There is floor space to set up a cushion, a yoga mat, or simply to move.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Longer stays</h3>
      <p>
        The kitchen includes a full-sized cooker, fridge, kettle, washing
        machine, and what is needed for a longer self-catering stay. A full
        inventory is available on request.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Outside</p>
      <h2>The grounds</h2>
      <p>
        The cabin sits within a half-acre plot surrounded by farmland. It is
        private and completely separate from the neighbouring houses. The garden
        has a lawn, patio, and mature trees, good for walking practice, sitting
        outside, or simply being in the open air. There are birds and wildlife.
      </p>
      <p>
        To maintain the half-acre, gardeners attend approximately once a
        fortnight. They work outside only and guests are not expected to
        interact with them, though they may briefly be aware of their presence.
        Wherever possible this falls on a fixed day, with details in the welcome
        note.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-panel">
      <p class="small-label">Local area</p>
      <ul class="list-clean">
        <li>Itteringham village shop and cafe: around 20 minutes on foot.</li>
        <li>Blickling Hall: about 1.5 miles by road and track.</li>
        <li>Aylsham: 4 miles.</li>
        <li>Norfolk coast: around 10 miles north.</li>
        <li>Norwich: 16.6 miles south.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Who this is for</p>
    <h2>The right guest</h2>
    <p>
      This is not a holiday cottage. It is a retreat space. The absence of
      television, internet, and distraction is not a limitation; it is the whole
      point.
    </p>
    <div class="fit-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>Good fit</h3>
        <ul class="list-clean">
          <li>Solo meditation or mindfulness retreat.</li>
          <li>Writing, creative work, or study.</li>
          <li>Recovery from burnout or illness.</li>
          <li>Grief, transition, or a major life threshold.</li>
          <li>Spiritual or contemplative practice.</li>
          <li>A genuine digital detox.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Probably not for you</h3>
        <ul class="list-clean">
          <li>You need constant internet access.</li>
          <li>You want a base for exploring Norfolk.</li>
          <li>You are looking for luxury or modern comforts.</li>
          <li>You dislike silence.</li>
          <li>You want a romantic break for two.</li>
          <li>You are booking for more than one person.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Preparation</p>
      <h2>What to bring</h2>
      <p>
        Guests bring their own linen, towels, and kitchen towels. Please also
        bring whatever practice materials you need: cushion, altar items, books,
        art materials, or anything else that supports your time here.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is not a serviced property. Guests are responsible for cleaning the
        cabin before they leave. Instructions and cleaning materials are
        provided.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-panel">
      <p class="small-label">Cleaning</p>
      <p>
        If the cabin requires a professional clean on departure, this will be
        charged at £100. The £150 deposit covers this and any electricity
        balance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2>Simple rates, with support available</h2>
      <div class="detail-grid">
        <article>
          <h3>Standard</h3>
          <p>Both summer and winter.</p>
          <p><strong>£50 per night</strong></p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Supported summer</h3>
          <p>Easter to the end of October half term.</p>
          <p><strong>£40 per night</strong></p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Supported winter</h3>
          <p>November to Easter.</p>
          <p><strong>£35 per night</strong></p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <p>
        Supported rates are available on request with no explanation needed,
        for meditators, dharma practitioners, and anyone for whom the standard
        rate is a genuine obstacle.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="price-panel">
      <p class="small-label">Stay length</p>
      <strong>5-28 nights</strong>
      <p>20% off for stays of 15-28 nights.</p>
      <p>Electricity is charged at cost, based on meter readings taken at arrival and departure.</p>
      <p>£150 deposit required on booking.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="statement quote-statement">
    <p>A space that holds you.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="contact-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Enquiries</p>
      <h2>Get in touch before booking</h2>
      <p>
        If you are not sure whether the cabin is right for your retreat, or if
        you are planning a longer stay, JaneCatherine is happy to talk it
        through before you book.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@stillground.co.uk">Email JaneCatherine</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
